{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848724614,"sessionID":"ses_2872b99f5ffeftnzqyRZm3uri5","part":{"id":"prt_d78d5148b001Er3OAkkOJRnk6D","messageID":"msg_d78d4f55f001chQ5ClZ7H7RuL4","sessionID":"ses_2872b99f5ffeftnzqyRZm3uri5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-20dc8d594fd341e99cacacb5303eadb8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Deploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Helm chart installation\n9: The system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n12: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n13: - **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n14: - **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\n17: The system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n20: - **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values\n21: - **WHEN** pods for `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router` start\n22: - **THEN** each container SHALL have environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` populated from those values\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Workload Manager deployment shape\n25: The system SHALL deploy Workload Manager as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `workloadmanager` with replica count, container image, service type/port, resource requests/limits, health probes, and optional `extraEnv` driven from `values.yaml`.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Default replica and service exposure\n28: - **GIVEN** default chart values\n29: - **WHEN** the chart is installed\n30: - **THEN** the Workload Manager `Deployment` SHALL use `workloadmanager.replicas` (default 1), expose HTTP on `workloadmanager.service.port` (default 8080), and use liveness/readiness HTTP GET `/health` on that port\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Router deployment shape\n33: The system SHALL deploy the Router as a `Deployment` and `Service` named `agentcube-router` with replica count, image, `ClusterIP` service mapping `port`→`targetPort`, resource requests/limits, optional dedicated `serviceAccountName`, and `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` pointing at the in-cluster Workload Manager service.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Router reaches Workload Manager by DNS\n36: - **GIVEN** release namespace `N` and Workload Manager service port `P` from values\n37: - **WHEN** the Router pod starts\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL have `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` set to `http://workloadmanager.N.svc.cluster.local:P` and container args including `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Workload Manager ClusterRole permissions\n41: The system SHALL create a `ServiceAccount` `workloadmanager`, a `ClusterRole` `workloadmanager`, and `ClusterRoleBinding` `workloadmanager` granting the rules required for agent-sandbox, AgentCube runtime CRDs, core workloads, auth, and secrets.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Binding ties SA to cluster role\n44: - **GIVEN** chart installation in namespace `N`\n45: - **WHEN** RBAC resources are applied\n46: - **THEN** subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `N` SHALL be bound to `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` via `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: Optional Router namespace Role\n49: The system SHALL optionally create namespace-scoped `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router when `router.rbac.create` is true, granting secret management in that namespace.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: RBAC off by default\n52: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false`\n53: - **WHEN** the chart renders templates\n54: - **THEN** Router optional RBAC manifests SHALL NOT be emitted\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: RBAC on with named service account\n57: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: true` and `router.serviceAccountName` set (or defaulted by template to `agentcube-router`)\n58: - **WHEN** the chart is applied\n59: - **THEN** Router pods MAY use that `serviceAccountName` and the Role SHALL allow verbs on `secrets` in the release namespace\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler\n62: The system SHALL optionally deploy Volcano agent scheduler resources (ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment) when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Scheduler disabled\n65: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n66: - **WHEN** templates render\n67: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler objects SHALL be created\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with the chart\n70: The system SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests for `agentruntimes` and `codeinterpreters` under the chart `crds/` directory so Helm installs them with the chart lifecycle.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: CRD group and scope\n73: - **GIVEN** chart path `manifests/charts/base`\n74: - **WHEN** CRD YAML is applied\n75: - **THEN** both CRDs SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, and `scope: Namespaced`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n78: The system SHALL provide Dockerfiles to build three images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`).\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Multi-stage Go build for control plane\n81: - **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n82: - **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile` (or `Dockerfile.router`) runs\n83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n84: \n85: ### Requirement: Makefile build targets\n86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Default `make` builds workload manager\n89: - **GIVEN** Go toolchain and generated code prerequisites\n90: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make` (default `all` → `build`)\n91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: E2E entrypoint\n94: - **GIVEN** Kind, kubectl, Docker, Helm, and curl available\n95: - **WHEN** the operator runs `make e2e`\n96: - **THEN** the repository SHALL execute `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` which provisions the cluster (unless skipped), deploys dependencies, and runs Go and Python E2E tests\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Specification\n\n## Purpose\nDeploy AgentCube control-plane components (Workload Manager, Router), optional Volcano agent scheduler, and required Redis connectivity via the `agentcube` Helm chart, container images, and Makefile-driven builds.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Helm chart installation\nThe system SHALL support installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`, including namespace creation and values for Redis, images, replicas, and optional router RBAC.\n\n#### Scenario: Install with release namespace\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster and Helm 3 available\n- **WHEN** the operator runs `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with required `redis.addr` (and optional `redis.password`) plus component image overrides as needed\n- **THEN** chart templates apply Workload Manager and Router workloads (and optional Volcano resources when enabled) in `<ns>` without manual editing of rendered YAML\n\n### Requirement: Helm values and Redis connectivity\nThe system SHALL require Redis address configuration for Workload Manager and Router at runtime via chart values `redis.addr` and `redis.password` (empty password permitted when Redis has no auth).\n\n#### Scenario: Components receive Redis env vars\n- **GIVEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` set in Helm values","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/spec.md","time":{"start":1775848724602,"end":1775848724612}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848724617,"sessionID":"ses_2872b99f5ffeftnzqyRZm3uri5","part":{"id":"prt_d78d517fe001Kywi0OKARJ6viK","messageID":"msg_d78d4f55f001chQ5ClZ7H7RuL4","sessionID":"ses_2872b99f5ffeftnzqyRZm3uri5","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a6fe90d351924fd6ba28ca702b6d15c9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n10: \n11: ### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n12: \n13: The system SHALL define the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n14: \n15: #### Scenario: Package structure exists\n16: - **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n17: - **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n18: - **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n19:   - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n20:   - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n21:   - `agentruntime_types.go` with `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types\n22:   - `codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types\n23:   - `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (generated)\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Scheme group version is correct\n26: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n27: - **WHEN** reading the file\n28: - **THEN** `SchemeGroupVersion` SHALL be `schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Group version kind registration\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n32: - **WHEN** the `addKnownTypes` function is invoked\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL register `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeList`, `CodeInterpreter`, and `CodeInterpreterList` with the scheme\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime type definition\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntime` as a Kubernetes-style typed object with `TypeMeta`, `ObjectMeta`, `Spec`, and `Status`.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime struct shape\n42: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n43: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntime` struct definition\n44: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta` and have `Spec AgentRuntimeSpec` and `Status AgentRuntimeStatus` fields with JSON tags `spec` and `status`\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeList struct shape\n47: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n48: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeList` struct definition\n49: - **THEN** the struct SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta`, have `metav1.ListMeta` with JSON tag `metadata`, and `Items []AgentRuntime` with JSON tag `items`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: CRD markers on AgentRuntime\n52: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n53: - **WHEN** examining type-level markers\n54: - **THEN** the `AgentRuntime` type SHALL have:\n55:   - `+genclient` marker\n56:   - `+k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object` marker\n57:   - `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` marker\n58:   - `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` marker\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeSpec definition\n63: \n64: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeSpec` with required fields for session management and pod templating.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec fields\n67: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n68: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct\n69: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n70:   - `MaxSessionDuration string` with JSON tag `maxSessionDuration`\n71:   - `SessionTimeout string` with JSON tag `sessionTimeout`\n72:   - `TargetPort []TargetPort` with JSON tag `targetPort`\n73:   - `PodTemplate PodTemplateSpec` with JSON tag `podTemplate`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec required fields\n76: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n77: - **WHEN** examining the `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct markers\n78: - **THEN** the struct SHALL have `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` or equivalent kubebuilder markers for `maxSessionDuration`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`, and `podTemplate` fields\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: MaxSessionDuration default\n81: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n82: - **WHEN** examining the `MaxSessionDuration` field marker\n83: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"8h\"` marker\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: SessionTimeout default\n86: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n87: - **WHEN** examining the `SessionTimeout` field marker\n88: - **THEN** it SHALL have `+kubebuilder:default=\"15m\"` marker\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ### Requirement: TargetPort type definition\n93: \n94: The system SHALL define `TargetPort` to specify how traffic is routed to the agent runtime pod.\n95: \n96: #### Scenario: TargetPort struct fields\n97: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n98: - **WHEN** reading the `TargetPort` struct\n99: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n100:   - `Port int32` with JSON tag `port` (required)\n101:   - `Protocol ProtocolType` with JSON tag `protocol` (enum: HTTP, HTTPS)\n102:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (optional)\n103:   - `PathPrefix string` with JSON tag `pathPrefix` (optional)\n104: \n105: #### Scenario: ProtocolType enum definition\n106: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n107: - **WHEN** reading the `ProtocolType` type definition\n108: - **THEN** it SHALL be a string type with `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum=HTTP;HTTPS` marker and constants `ProtocolHTTP` and `ProtocolHTTPS`\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: AgentRuntimeStatus definition\n113: \n114: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with standard Kubernetes condition fields.\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeStatus fields\n117: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n118: - **WHEN** reading the `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct\n119: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain `Conditions []metav1.Condition` with JSON tag `conditions`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Conditions field markers\n122: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go`\n123: - **WHEN** examining the `Conditions` field\n124: - **THEN** it SHALL have:\n125:   - `+kubebuilder:validation:Optional` marker\n126:   - `+listType=map` marker\n127:   - `+listMapKey=type` marker\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: DeepCopy generation\n132: \n133: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy` methods for all types using controller-gen.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntime\n136: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go` (after `make generate`)\n137: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n138: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntime) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntime)` SHALL exist and correctly copy all nested fields including `Spec.TargetPort` slice\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeList\n141: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n142: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n143: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeList) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeList)` SHALL exist and correctly copy `Items` slice\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeSpec\n146: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n147: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n148: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeSpec) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeSpec)` SHALL exist\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for TargetPort\n151: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n152: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n153: - **THEN** `func (in *TargetPort) DeepCopyInto(out *TargetPort)` SHALL exist\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: DeepCopyInto for AgentRuntimeStatus\n156: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/zz_generated.deepcopy.go`\n157: - **WHEN** examining generated code\n158: - **THEN** `func (in *AgentRuntimeStatus) DeepCopyInto(out *AgentRuntimeStatus)` SHALL exist\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ### Requirement: CRD generation\n163: \n164: The system SHALL generate CRD YAML that matches the expected schema from `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`.\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: CRD generation command\n167: - **GIVEN** the repository with types defined in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n168: - **WHEN** running `make gen-crd`\n169: - **THEN** the command SHALL invoke `controller-gen crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/... output:dir=manifests/charts/base/crds`\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Generated CRD metadata\n172: - **GIVEN** the generated `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n173: - **WHEN** examining the CRD\n174: - **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n175: - AND `spec.group` SHALL be `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n176: - AND `spec.names.kind` SHALL be `AgentRuntime`\n177: - AND `spec.names.plural` SHALL be `agentruntimes`\n178: - AND `spec.scope` SHALL be `Namespaced`\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Generated CRD version\n181: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n182: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions`\n183: - **THEN** there SHALL be exactly one version with `name: v1alpha1`, `served: true`, and `storage: true`\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Generated CRD spec schema\n186: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n187: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions[0].schema.openAPIV3Schema.properties.spec`\n188: - **THEN** the `required` array SHALL include `maxSessionDuration`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`, and `podTemplate`\n189: - AND `properties.maxSessionDuration.default` SHALL be `\"8h\"`\n190: - AND `properties.sessionTimeout.default` SHALL be `\"15m\"`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Generated CRD status subresource\n193: - **GIVEN** the generated CRD\n194: - **WHEN** examining `spec.versions[0]`\n195: - **THEN** `subresources.status` SHALL be present\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### Requirement: Client-go code generation compatibility\n200: \n201: The system SHALL define types compatible with `k8s.io/code-generator` for generating typed clients, informers, and listers.\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Group version registration for client-gen\n204: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`\n205: - **WHEN** reading the file\n206: - **THEN** `SchemeBuilder` SHALL be defined using `NewSchemeBuilder` and `AddToScheme` SHALL be exposed as `localSchemeBuilder.AddToScheme(scheme)`\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Types implement runtime.Object\n209: - **GIVEN** the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types\n210: - **WHEN** the DeepCopy methods are generated\n211: - **THEN** both types SHALL implement `runtime.Object` interface via `DeepCopyObject()` method\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Client generation command\n214: - **GIVEN** types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n215: - **WHEN** running `make gen-client`\n216: - **THEN** `hack/update-codegen.sh` SHALL be invoked, which runs `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with:\n217:   - `--with-watch` flag\n218:   - `--output-dir client-go`\n219:   - `--output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n220:   - Input API at `runtime/v1alpha1`\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Generated typed client exists\n223: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n224: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n225: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeInterface` SHALL define methods: `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `DeleteCollection`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Generated informer exists\n228: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n229: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n230: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeInformer` interface SHALL define `Informer() cache.SharedIndexInformer` and `Lister() runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister`\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Generated lister exists\n233: - **GIVEN** client-go code generation completed\n234: - **WHEN** examining `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n235: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeLister` interface SHALL define `List(selector labels.Selector)` and `AgentRuntimes(namespace string)` methods\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime Type Definition\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Package structure and registration\n\nThe system SHALL define the `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeList` types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` with proper package structure, scheme registration, and CRD markers for controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: Package structure exists\n- **GIVEN** the repository root at `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- **WHEN** examining `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n- **THEN** the directory SHALL contain:\n  - `doc.go` with `+k8s:deepcopy-gen=package` marker\n  - `register.go` with `SchemeGroupVersion` set to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848724605,"end":1775848724615}}}}
